Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Hi, thank you working on this! As for me the whole idea is great and I completely agree with the refactoring. But it's at least breaks the existing API, so ApiImpact flag in commit message must be added.

I will examine the seriousness of your changes and give you detailed response soon.

Patch Set 4:

I have reverted the backward breaking compatibility change for this patch. However the spec for "Show image member details" (http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-image-v2.html#getImageMember-v2) doesn't specify that we should return NotFound instead of Forbidden. I have opened a bug (#1450370) to change this current behavior. Please comment on the bug.
